description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Urology Department, for an experienced, motivated and flexible Senior Medical Secretary to contribute to the delivery of high quality care to our patients and to provide a full secretarial support to Consultants and the clinical team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Urology is a busy speciality, providing inpatient and daycase procedures for a wide range of conditions. You will be responsible for the patient pathway management for a consultant led team, whilst balancing the need to adhere to national and local targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have good communication skills and will be responsive to the needs of the service. You will be a point of contact for patients, speciality teams and other departments for all enquiries relating to the Urology service. Previous Line Management experience is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An awareness of the NHS and related targets would be advantageous. However, close working relationship with the Admin and Performance Co-ordinator will ensure smooth running of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSarah BeatonJob titleSenior Medical SecretaryEmail addresssarah.beaton@nhs.netTelephone number01733 677482&lt;/p&gt;
